    </div>
</div>
</article>
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES790105971" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK MEDIAPROMO PRIMARY" -->
   <p>"I think part of this may be bluff on their part. They think the president's desperate for a deal, and if they put an artificial time constraint on it, they may think they're going to get a better deal. We'll just have to wait and see," he said.</p>   <p>"But this is all part of the North Korean playbook. They've successfully jived the three prior American administrations, and they plan to do the same with this one."</p>   <p>And he thinks the administration is making a "big mistake" if — <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/09/world/asia/north-korea-trump.html">as reported by The New York Times</a> — it stymied attempts by the United Nations Security Council to hold a discussion on North Korea's human rights abuses, for fear of upsetting North Korea and thereby derailing nuclear negotiations.</p>   <p>"It's been the pattern as we've watched it for over three decades now: The North Koreans are very happy to declare that they're going to give up their nuclear weapons program, particularly when it's in exchange for tangible economic benefits, but they never get around to doing it," said Bolton.</p>   <aside id="ad-backstage-wrap" aria-label="advertisement">
    

    <div id="ad-backstage-News_World" class="ad-backstage" data-ad-config='{"network":"\/6735\/","site":{"default":"n6735.NPR","mobile":"n6735.NPRMOBILE"},"zone":"News_World","targets":{"testserver":"false","isPodcastEpisode":"false","storyId":"789821202","program":"Morning_Edition","agg":["191676894","593868387","434975886"]},"location":"backstage","deferred":false,"isBetweenContent":true,"isAggSponsorship":false,"borderClass":""}'></div>

</aside>   <p>"And I think the inescapable conclusion is that they're happy to sell that same bridge over and over again, but there's no serious chance they will ever voluntarily give it up."</p>   <div id="res789984031" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage789933563" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/12/19/789933563/transcript-nprs-full-interview-with-john-bolton"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/12\/19\/789933563\/transcript-nprs-full-interview-with-john-bolton"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/12/19/ap_19273516805549_sq-0c2f3f723c791ed5ae404e00da9ba5b4fbfdef8e-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/12/19/ap_19273516805549_sq-0c2f3f723c791ed5ae404e00da9ba5b4fbfdef8e-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Transcript: NPR's Full Interview With John Bolton" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/12/19/789933563/transcript-nprs-full-interview-with-john-bolton"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/12\/19\/789933563\/transcript-nprs-full-interview-with-john-bolton"}' >Transcript: NPR's Full Interview With John Bolton</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES789984031" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <div id="res789977039" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage724363700" href="https://www.npr.org/2019/09/10/724363700/trump-fires-john-bolton-in-final-break-after-months-of-policy-divisions"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/09\/10\/724363700\/trump-fires-john-bolton-in-final-break-after-months-of-policy-divisions"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/05/17/ap_19121457462116_sq-6fabd08ea8fbca49c551e0799cae12bea490750a-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/05/17/ap_19121457462116_sq-6fabd08ea8fbca49c551e0799cae12bea490750a-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Trump Fires John Bolton In Final Break After Months Of Internal Policy Division" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/national-security/">National Security </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/09/10/724363700/trump-fires-john-bolton-in-final-break-after-months-of-policy-divisions"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2019\/09\/10\/724363700\/trump-fires-john-bolton-in-final-break-after-months-of-policy-divisions"}' >Trump Fires John Bolton In Final Break After Months Of Internal Policy Division</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES789977039" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Bolton's comments represent a stark break — <a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/09/30/765721764/ousted-national-security-adviser-bolton-slams-trumps-approach-to-north-korea">but not a surprising one</a> — with the administration he served before his ouster three months ago. The foreign policy hawk and the president had butted heads repeatedly over the direction of the administration's national security policy.</p>   <p>Now, Bolton has found himself at the center of the political maelstrom over the impeachment of the president, with Democratic lawmakers seeking — <a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/12/17/788924966/mcconnell-i-m-not-impartial-about-impeachment">and so far failing</a> — to obtain his testimony about Trump's decision to withhold U.S. military aid to Ukraine.</p>   <p>As for their differences on North Korea, Trump has actively pursued a deal with the nuclear state throughout much of his time in office — though that diplomatic pursuit has fallen on tough times lately.</p>   <p>The promise of talks and a landmark agreement, seemingly so close when North Korean leader Kim Jong Un met Trump for the first time <a href="https://www.npr.org/2019/06/30/737365074/trump-to-meet-kim-jong-un-at-dmz">last year</a>, has devolved into an exchange of bellicose rhetoric.</p>   <div id="res789987318" class="bucketwrap image large">
            <div class="imagewrap" data-crop-type="">
    <img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/12/19/gettyimages-1158941986_slide-2abb14d9690deef9a7fb3b9c7e8dc87c4e990aee-s1100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/12/19/gettyimages-1158941986_slide-2abb14d9690deef9a7fb3b9c7e8dc87c4e990aee-s1100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="" />
        <div class="enlarge-options">
            <a class="enlargelink" href="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2019/12/19/gettyimages-1158941986_slide-2abb14d9690deef9a7fb3b9c7e8dc87c4e990aee-s1200.jpg">Enlarge this image</a>
        </div>
</div>
<div class="credit-caption">
    <div class="caption-wrap">
        <div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption">
